ke for boating/fishing & a seasonal, outdoor water park. Contact us at (573) 874-7111. Visit our website at...\",\"address\":{\"@type\":\"PostalAddress\",\"addressLocality\":\"Columbia\",\"addressRegion\":\"MO\",\"addressCountry\":\"US\"}}},{\"@type\":\"ListItem\",\"position\":5,\"item\":{\"@type\":\"SportsActivityLocation\",\"@id\":\"https://www.indoordogpark.org/parks/dog-park\",\"name\":\"Dog Park\",\"url\":\"https://www.indoordogpark.org/parks/dog-park\",\"description\":\"Dog Park is a favorite spot for dog owners in Columbia.\\n\\nThis park is well-equipped with amenities such as indoor facilities for all-weather play, climate-controlled areas, professional staff...\",\"address\":{\"@type\":\"PostalAddress\",\"addressLocality\":\"Columbia\",\"addressRegion\":\"MO\",\"addressCountry\":\"US\"}}},{\"@type\":\"ListItem\",\"position\":6,\"item\":{\"@type\":\"SportsActivityLocation\",\"@id\":\"https://www.indoordogpark.org/parks/noma-north-main-bark-park-members-only\",\"name\":\"NOMA (North Main) Bark Park - Members only\",\"url\":\"https://www.indoordogpark.org/parks/noma-north-main-bark-park-members-only\",\"description\":\"NOMA (North Main) Bark Park - Members only provides a safe and fun environment for dogs of all sizes in the heart of Columbia.\\n\\nThis park is well-equipped with amenities such as indoor facilities for...\",\"address\":{\"@type\":\"PostalAddress\",\"addressLocality\":\"Columbia\",\"addressRegion\":\"MO\",\"addressCountry\":\"US\"}}}]}</script><script type=\"application/ld+json\">{\"@context\":\"https://schema.org\",\"@type\":\"FAQPage\",\"mainEntity\":[{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"What are the best dog parks in Columbia, MO?\",\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"Columbia is known for its \\\"leash-free\\\" areas. Twin Lakes Recreation Area offers a dog park with lake access, and the Garth Nature Area provides a large fenced space for running.\"}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"Where can I take my dog swimming in Columbia?\",\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"Twin Lakes Recreation Area is the go-to spot during the season, featuring a dedicated dog swim area. Stephens Lake Park also has designated lake access points for dogs.\"}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"Are there dog-friendly trails in Columbia?\",\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"Yes, the MKT Trail is a premier crushed-limestone trail perfect for dog walking. It connects the city to the Katy Trail State Park.\"}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"Is downtown Columbia pet-friendly?\",\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"very. The District (downtown) features many dog-friendly restaurant patios and shops. It is a vibrant area to explore with your pup, especially on weekends.\"}}]}</script><script type=\"application/ld+json\">{\"@context\":\"https://schema.org\",\"@type\":\"BreadcrumbList\",\"itemListElement\":[{\"@type\":\"ListItem\",\"position\":1,\"name\":\"Home\",\"item\":\"https://www.indoordogpark.org/\"},{\"@type\":\"ListItem\",\"position\":2,\"name\":\"Dog Parks Directory\",\"item\":\"https://www.indoordogpark.org/\"},{\"@type\":\"ListItem\",\"position\":3,\"name\":\"Columbia\"}]}</script><header class=\"header header-visible  header-light\"><div class=\"header-container\"><div class=\"header-left\"><a class=\"logo\" href=\"/\"><img alt=\"Indoor Dog Park logo\" width=\"140\" height=\"40\" decoding=\"async\" data-nimg=\"1\" style=\"color:transparent;object-fit:contain;height:auto\" src=\"/images/logo/logo.png\"/></a></div><div class=\"header-center\"><nav class=\"header-nav\" aria-label=\"Main navigation\"><a class=\"header-nav-link\" href=\"/\">Browse Parks</a><div class=\"header-nav-item\"><button class=\"header-nav-link\" aria-haspopup=\"true\" aria-expanded=\"false\">Discover <i class=\"bi bi-chevron-down dropdown-icon \"></i></button><div class=\"header-dropdown \"><a class=\"header-dropdown-link\" href=\"/parks-with-bars\">Parks with Bars</a><a class=\"heade