mbia\",\"addressRegion\":\"MO\",\"addressCountry\":\"US\"}}},{\"@type\":\"ListItem\",\"position\":5,\"item\":{\"@type\":\"SportsActivityLocation\",\"@id\":\"https://www.indoordogpark.org/parks/dog-park\",\"name\":\"Dog Park\",\"url\":\"https://www.indoordogpark.org/parks/dog-park\",\"description\":\"Dog Park is a favorite spot for dog owners in Columbia.\\n\\nThis park is well-equipped with amenities such as indoor facilities for all-weather play, climate-controlled areas, professional staff...\",\"address\":{\"@type\":\"PostalAddress\",\"addressLocality\":\"Columbia\",\"addressRegion\":\"MO\",\"addressCountry\":\"US\"}}},{\"@type\":\"ListItem\",\"position\":6,\"item\":{\"@type\":\"SportsActivityLocation\",\"@id\":\"https://www.indoordogpark.org/parks/noma-north-main-bark-park-members-only\",\"name\":\"NOMA (North Main) Bark Park - Members only\",\"url\":\"https://www.indoordogpark.org/parks/noma-north-main-bark-park-members-only\",\"description\":\"NOMA (North Main) Bark Park - Members only provides a safe and fun environment for dogs of all sizes in the heart of Columbia.\\n\\nThis park is well-equipped with amenities such as indoor facilities for...\",\"address\":{\"@type\":\"PostalAddress\",\"addressLocality\":\"Columbia\",\"addressRegion\":\"MO\",\"addressCountry\":\"US\"}}}]}3:[\"$\",\"script\",null,{\"type\":\"application/ld+json\",\"suppressHydrationWarning\":true,\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"$c\"}}]\nd:T495,{\"@context\":\"https://schema.org\",\"@type\":\"FAQPage\",\"mainEntity\":[{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"What are the best dog parks in Columbia, MO?\",\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"Columbia is known for its \\\"leash-free\\\" areas. Twin Lakes Recreation Area offers a dog park with lake access, and the Garth Nature Area provides a large fenced space for running.\"}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"Where can I take my dog swimming in Columbia?\",\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"Twin Lakes Recreation Area is the go-to spot during the season, featuring a dedicated dog swim area. Stephens Lake Park also has designated lake access points for dogs.\"}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"Are there dog-friendly trails in Columbia?\",\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"Yes, the MKT Trail is a premier crushed-limestone trail perfect for dog walking. It connects the city to the Katy Trail State Park.\"}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"Is downtown Columbia pet-friendly?\",\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"very. The District (downtown) features many dog-friendly restaurant patios and shops. It is a vibrant area to explore with your pup, especially on weekends.\"}}]}4:[\"$\",\"script\",null,{\"type\":\"application/ld+json\",\"suppressHydrationWarning\":true,\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"$d\"}}]\n5:[\"$\",\"script\",null,{\"type\":\"application/ld+json\",\"suppressHydrationWarning\":true,\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"{\\\"@context\\\":\\\"https://schema.org\\\",\\\"@type\\\":\\\"BreadcrumbList\\\",\\\"itemListElement\\\":[{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"ListItem\\\",\\\"position\\\":1,\\\"name\\\":\\\"Home\\\",\\\"item\\\":\\\"https://www.indoordogpark.org/\\\"},{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"ListItem\\\",\\\"position\\\":2,\\\"name\\\":\\\"Dog Parks Directory\\\",\\\"item\\\":\\\"https://www.indoordogpark.org/\\\"},{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"ListItem\\\",\\\"position\\\":3,\\\"name\\\":\\\"Columbia\\\"}]}\"}}]\n6:[\"$\",\"$Le\",null,{\"variant\":\"light\"}]\n7:[\"$\",\"$Lf\",null,{\"items\":[{\"id\":\"city-hero\",\"title\":\"City Overview\",\"level\":1},{\"id\":\"city-insights\",\"title\":\"Quick Facts\",\"level\":1},{\"id\":\"city-comparison\",\"title\":\"Top Comparisons\",\"level\":1},{\"id\":\"park-collections\",\"title\":\"Park Collections\",\"level\":1},{\"id\":\"neighborhood-clusters\",\"title\":\"Neighborhoods\",\"level\":1},{\"id\":\"park-types-guide\",\"title\":\"Park Type Guide\",\"level\":1},{\"id\":\"map-and-neighborhoods\",\"title\":\"Map & Neighborhoods\",\"level\":1},{\"id\":\"planning-essentials\",\"title\":\"Planning Essentials\",\"level\":1},{\"id\":\"expert-tips\",\"title\":\"Expert Advice\",\"level\":1},{\"id\":\"park-directory\",\"title\":\"Full Directory\",\"level\":1},{\"id\":\"owner-cta\",\"title\":\"Owner & Franchise\",\"level\":1},{\"id\":\"faq-section\",\"title\":\"FAQs\",\"level\":1},{\"id\":\"related-resources\",\"title\":\"More Resources\",\"level\":1}]}]\n8:[\"$\",\"main\",null,{\"className\":\"city-page-layout\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"mobile-toc-button\",\"children\":[\"$\",\"$L10\",null,{\"className\":\"mobile-toc-trigger\",\"targetSelector\":\".table-of-contents\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"i\",null,{\"className\":\"bi bi-list-ul\"}],[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"children\":\"Contents\"}]]}]}],[\"$\",\"section\",null,{\"id\":\"city-hero\",\"className\":\"city-hero-section \",\"children\":[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"section-shell city-hero-shell\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"city-hero-copy\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"hero-breadcrumbs\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"$L11\",null,{\"href\":\"/\",\"children\":\"Home\"}],[\"$\",\"i\",null,{\"className\":\"bi bi-chevron-right\"}],[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"children\":\"Dog Parks Directory\"}],[\"$\",\"i\",null,{\"className\":\"bi bi-chevron-right\"}],[\"$\",\"strong\",null,{\"children\":\"Columbia\"}]]}],[\"$\",\"p\",null,{\"className\":\"hero-eyebrow\",\"children\":\"City spotlight\"}],[\"$\",\"h1\",null,{\"children\":\"Indoor Dog Park In Columbia\"}],\"$undefined\",[\"$\",\"p\",null,{\"className\":\"hero-description\",\"children\":\"Explore leash-free parks and indoor services in Columbia, MO. Discover the best spots for swimming and socializing your dog.\"}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"city-rich-description\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"p\",\"0\",{\"className\":\"rich-description-paragraph\",\"children\":[\"Columbia is widely recognized as one of the most dog-friendly cities in the Midwest, famous for its unique 'leash-free' recreational areas. Parks like Twin Lakes and Garth Nature Area offer vast, open spaces where dogs can run without the confinement of traditional fences, a rarity in urban planning. While a dedicated building for indoor dog parking is not a standard municipal offering, the city's youthful, college-town energy fuels a high demand for dog services, resulting in numerous indoor daycare and training options.\"]}],[\"$\",\"p\",\"1\",{\"className\":\"rich-description-paragraph\",\"children\":[\"The University of Missouri's presence brings a population that loves to include pets in their daily lives. This is reflected in the bustling downtown District, where dogs are a staple on restaurant patios and in shop windows. The availability of water access for dogs at Twin Lakes is a massive draw during humid summers. Columbia's approach to dog ownership emphasizes freedom and socialization, making it an exciting place for dogs to explore and interact.\"]}]]}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"hero-cta-row\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"$L10\",null,{\"className\":\"hero-cta primary\",\"targetId\":\"park-directory\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"i\",null,{\"className\":\"bi bi-list-check\"}],\"Browse directory\"]}],[\"$\",\"$L10\",null,{\"className\":\"hero-cta ghost\",\"targetId\":\"map-and-neighborhoods\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"i\",null,{\"className\":\"bi bi-geo-alt\"}],\"Open map\"]}],[\"$\",\"$L11\",null,{\"href\":\"/list-your-park\",\"className\":\"hero-cta text-link\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"i\",null,{\"className\":\"bi bi-plus-circle\"}],\"Submit a park\"]}]]}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"hero-footnotes\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"span\",\"Data refreshed weekly\",{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"i\",null,{\"className\":\"bi bi-sparkles\"}],\" \",\"Data refreshed weekly\"]}],[\"$\",\"span\",\"Live availability coming soon\",{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"i\",null,{\"className\":\"bi bi-sparkles\"}],\" \",\"Live availability coming soon\"]}]]}]]}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"city-hero-visual\",\"children\":[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"hero-image-card\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"$L12\",null,{\"src\":\"/images/cities/columbia-mo/hero.webp\",\"alt\":\"Columbia dog park landscape\",\"fill\":true,\"priority\":true,\"sizes\":\"(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 540px\",\"unoptimized\":true}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"hero-image-gradient\"}]]}]}]]}]}],[\"$\",\"$L13\",null,{\"city\":\"Columbia\",\"state\":\"MO\"}],[\"$\",\"section\",null,{\"id\":\"city-insights\",\"className\":\"city-insights-section\",\"children\":[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"section-shell\",\"children\":[\"$\",\"$L14\",null,{\"parks\":[{\"id\":\"ChIJufU9U-jJ3IcRm0R95I7cSDA\",\"name\":\"Columbia Cosmopolitan Recreation Area (Cosmo Park)\",\"businessType\":\"Dog Park\",\"description\":\"Columbia's largest park, with ball fields, tennis courts, a golf course, trails & fishing ponds. Contact us at (573) 874-7460. Visit our website at https://www.como.gov/parksandrec/park/columbia-cosmopolitan-recreation-area/.\",\"slug\":\"columbia-cosmopolitan-recreation-area-cosmo-park\",\"address\":\"1615 Business Loop 70 W\",\"street\":\"1615 Business Loop 70 W\",\"city\":\"Columbia\",\"state\":\"MO\",\"zipCode\":\"65202\",\"full_address\":\"1615 Business Loop 70 W, Columbia, MO 65202, USA\",\"latitude\":38.9696106,\"longitude\":-92.3632219,\"googlePlaceId\":\"ChIJufU9U-jJ3IcRm0R95I7cSDA\",\"phone\":\"(573) 874-7460\",\"website\":\"https://www.como.gov/parksandrec/park/columbia-cosmopolitan-recreation-area/\",\"photos\":null,\"rating\":4.7,\"reviewCount\":1702,\"openingHours\":{\"Monday\":\"6:00 AM – 12:00 AM\",\"Tuesday\":\"6:00 AM – 12:00 AM\",\"Wednesday\":\"6:00 AM – 12:00 AM\",\"Thursday\":\"6:00 AM – 12:00 AM\",\"Friday\":\"6:00 AM – 12:00 AM\",\"Saturday\":\"6:00 AM – 12:00 AM\",\"Sunday\":\"6:00 AM – 12:00 AM\"},\"amenities\":{\"Onsite services\":true,\"Indoor facilities\":true,\"Professional staff\":true,\"Climate controlled\":true,\"Wheelchair accessible entrance\":true,\"Parking available\":true,\"Easy access\":true},\"pricing\":{\"pricingSource\":\"website\",\"isFree\":false},\"placeTypes\":[\"point_of_interest\",\"establishment\"],\"lastUpdated\":null,\"dataQuality\":\"verified\",\"photo\":null,\"faqs\":[],\"source\":\"static\",\"listingType\":\"free\"},{\"id\":\"ChIJI2scnnfH3IcRJX63hK5iMgE\",\"name\":\"Dog Park\",\"businessType\":\"Dog Park\",\"description\":\"Dog Park is a favorite spot for dog owners in Columbia.\\n\\nThis park is well-equipped with amenities such as indoor facilities for all-weather play, climate-controlled areas, professional staff on-site, convenient onsite services, ensuring a comfortable visit for both you and your pet. With a solid 4.4-star rating from over 158 reviews, it's a highly recommended community favorite. Make sure to check the [official page](https://www.como.gov/dog-parks-leash-free-areas/) for membership info. For more dog-friendly spots, browse [Indoor Dog Park](https://www.indoordogpark.org/).\",\"slug\":\"dog-park\",\"address\":\"5009 Aztec Blvd\",\"street\":\"5009 Aztec Blvd\",\"city\":\"Columbia\",\"state\":\"MO\",\"zipCode\":\"65202\",\"full_address\":\"5009 Aztec Blvd, Columbia, MO 65202, USA\",\"latitude\":38.97727400000001,\"longitude\":-92.260578,\"googlePlaceId\":\"ChIJI2scnnfH3IcRJX63hK5iMgE\",\"phone\":\"\",\"website\":\"https://www.como.gov/dog-parks-leash-free-areas/\",\"photos\":null,\"rating\":4.4,\"reviewCount\":158,\"openingHours\":{\"Monday\":\"7:00 AM – 11:00 PM\",\"Tuesday\":\"7:00 AM – 11:00 PM\",\"Wednesday\":\"7:00 AM – 11:00 PM\",\"Thursday\":\"7:00 AM – 11:00 PM\",\"Friday\":\"7:00 AM – 11:00 PM\",\"Saturday\":\"7:00 AM – 11:00 PM\",\"Sunday\":\"7:00 AM – 11:00 PM\"},\"amenities\":{\"Onsite services\":true,\"Indoor facilities\":true,\"Professional staff\":true,\"Climate controlled\":true,\"Wheelchair accessible entrance\":true,\"Parking available\":true,\"Easy access\":true},\"pricing\":{\"pricingS